doc.ContractDescription: THE LAUNCH OF THE GOES-R IN MARCH 2016 WILL GREATLY ENHANCE THE SPATIOTEMPORAL COVERAGE AND RESOLUTION OF GEOSTATIONARY SATELLITEBASED OBSERVATIONS AND OUR ABILITY TO MONITOR RAPIDLY EVOLVING SEVERE WEATHER PHENOMENA, SUCH AS TORNADIC THUNDERSTORMS AND CONVECTIVE LINES. IN THIS PROJECT, THE ULTIMATE GOAL IS TO IMPROVE THE ANALYSIS, PREDICTION AND UNDERSTANDING OF TORNADIC THUNDERSTORMS THROUGH ADVANCED ENSEMBLE-BASED DATA ASSIMILATION TECHNIQUES THAT ARE ABLE TO INTEGRATE SATELLITE-BASED OBSERVATIONS ALONG WITH OTHER CONVENTIONAL, IN SITU AND REMOTE-SENSING OBSERVATIONS EFFICIENTLY, AND PRODUCE ENSEMBLE FORECASTS USING HIGH-RESOLUTION CONVECTIONALLOWING NUMERICAL WEATHER PREDICTION MODELS. THE SATELLITE OBSERVATIONS TO BE EXPLORED INCLUDE, BUT ARE NOT LIMITED TO, BRIGHTNESS TEMPERATURES, SATELLITE-DERIVED ATMOSPHERIC MOTION VECTORS (AMVS) AND TOTAL LIGHTNING ACTIVITY FROM THE GEOSTATIONARY LIGHTNING MAPPER (GLM) FROM GOES-R. MAJOR OBJECTIVES INCLUDE: 1. EXPLORE THE STRUCTURE AND DYNAMICS OF COVARIANCES BETWEEN BOTH CLOUD-AFFECTED AND CLEAR-SKY BRIGHTNESS TEMPERATURES AND STATE VARIABLES OF NUMERICAL MODELS WITHIN OR ASSOCIATED WITH TORNADIC THUNDERSTORMS AND CONVECTIVE LINES AND THEIR SURROUNDING ENVIRONMENTAL CONDITIONS THROUGH CONVECTION-ALLOWING ENSEMBLE FORECASTS USING THE WEATHER RESEARCH AND FORECASTING (WRF) MODEL THAT IS COUPLED WITH THE COMMUNITY RADIATIVE TRANSFER MODEL (CRTM). WE ALSO WILL EXPLORE THE STRUCTURE AND DYNAMICS OF COVARIANCES BETWEEN TOTAL LIGHTNING ACTIVITY AND MODEL STATE VARIABLES WITHIN TORNADIC THUNDERSTORMS, WITH A PARTICULAR FOCUS ON MODEL ICE-PHASE HYDROMETEORS. UNDERSTANDING THE COVARIANCES USING SUCH ENSEMBLE SENSITIVITY ANALYSIS IS ESSENTIAL TO IDENTIFYING THE APPROPRIATE SATELLITE OBSERVATIONS FOR DATA ASSIMILATION APPLICATIONS AND TO UNDERSTAND THEIR PROPERTIES AND CHARACTERISTICS. 2. CONDUCT EXTENSIVE AND SYSTEMATIC OBSERVING SYSTEM SIMULATION EXPERIMENTS (OSSES) FOR THE 20 MAY 2013 MOORE TORNADIC THUNDERSTORM EVENT BY ASSIMILATING SIMULATED BRIGHTNESS TEMPERATURES AND TOTAL LIGHTNING ACTIVITY UNDER VARYING DEGREES OF MODEL AND OBSERVATION ERRORS. THE OSSE CONTAINS A KNOWN SIMULATED TRUTH, THUS WILL BE HELPFUL IN QUANTIFYING THE IMPACT OF DIFFERENT SATELLITE OBSERVATIONS AND MODEL AND ENSEMBLE CONFIGURATIONS AS WELL AS THE EFFECTIVENESS OF DIFFERENT DATA ASSIMILATION TECHNIQUES. TOTAL LIGHTNING ACTIVITY CAN BE ESTIMATED FROM MODEL VALUES OF GRAUPEL FLUX AND VERTICALLY INTEGRATED GRAUPEL. TECHNIQUES THAT TREAT MODEL AND SAMPLING ERRORS IN ENSEMBLE-BASED DATA ASSIMILATION OF SATELLITE DATA, SUCH AS DIFFERENT METHODS OF RELAXATION, INFLATION AND LOCALIZATION, AND TECHNIQUES DESIGNED TO ASSIMILATE MULTI-SCALE OBSERVATIONS EFFECTIVELY ARE OF SPECIFIC INTEREST. 3. EXTENSIVE DATA ASSIMILATION EXPERIMENTS WILL BE CONDUCTED TO EXAMINE THE IMPACTS OF OBSERVATIONS FROM THE TO-BE-LAUNCHED GOESR SATELLITE ON THE ANALYSIS AND PREDICTION OF TORNADIC THUNDERSTORMS AND CONVECTIVE LINES. BECAUSE THE KEY INSTRUMENT ONBOARD THE HIMAWARI 8 SATELLITE OF JAPAN THAT WAS LAUNCHED IN OCTOBER 2014 IS SIMILAR TO THAT ONBOARD GOES-R, OBSERVATIONS FROM HIMAWARI 8 WILL BE USED AS A REAL-DATA TEST IN ADVANCE OF GOES-R OPERATIONS. THROUGH EXTENSIVE OBSERVING SYSTEM EXPERIMENTS THAT WITHHOLD OR ADD DIFFERENT SATELLITE OBSERVATIONS, WE WILL EXAMINE THE DIFFERENCES AND SIMILARITIES IN THE EFFECTIVENESS OF ASSIMILATING SATELLITE-BASED OBSERVATIONS (BRIGHTNESS TEMPERATURES, AMVS AND GLM) VERSUS GROUND-BASED REMOTE-SENSING OBSERVATIONS (WSR-88D OR NLDN) FOR MONITORING AND PREDICTING TORNADIC THUNDERSTORMS AND CONVECTIVE LINES. 4. BOTH THE SIMULATED AND REAL-DATA ENSEMBLE ANALYSIS AND FORECAST EXPERIMENTS WILL BE USED TO UNDERSTAND THE FORMATION, INTENSIFICATION AND PREDICTABILITY OF TORNADIC THUNDERSTORMS AND TO ASSESS IF SATELLITE-BASED PRODUCTS, COUPLED WITH ADVANCED ALGORITHMS AND MODELS, CAN RESULT IN MORE ACCURATE FORECASTS AND WARNINGS OF TORNADOES.

doc.ContractDescription: A NUMBER OF THEORIES HAVE BEEN ADVANCED FOR THE ORIGIN OF LIFE, MANY OF WHICH POSIT RNA OR RNA-LIKE MOLECULES AS BOTH INFORMATION CARRYING AND CATALYTIC ENTITIES, AND ALL OF WHICH ULTIMATELY REQUIRE COMPARTMENTALIZATION OF FUNCTIONAL MOLECULES TO FORM THE EARLIEST CELLS. THIS PROPOSAL INVESTIGATES PHYSICAL MEANS THAT MAY HAVE FACILITATED THE EMERGENCE OF LIFE THROUGH THE LOCALIZATION AND IMPROVEMENT OF RNA CATALYSIS. IT ADDRESSES THE QUESTION HOW DOES LIFE BEGIN AND EVOLVE?, FROM THE 2008 NASA ASTROBIOLOGY ROADMAP. SPECIFICALLY, IT SPEAKS TO GOAL 3, BY SEEKING TO UNDERSTAND GENERAL PHYSICAL AND CHEMICAL PRINCIPLES THAT LED TO THE FIRST CELLS. WE WILL EVALUATE COMPARTMENTALIZATION DRIVEN BY AQUEOUS PHASE SEPARATION AS A POTENTIAL PHYSICOCHEMICAL MECHANISM TO CONCENTRATE AND HELP CHAPERONE THE FOLDING, MULTIPLE TURNOVER, AND EVOLUTION OF RARE CATALYTIC RNA MOLECULES, AND TO FACILITATE THE FORMATION OF PROGENITOR MEMBRANES THAT ENCAPSULATE THESE MOLECULES WITH EXCEPTIONALLY HIGH EFFICIENCY AS A STEP TOWARDS THE FORMATION OF PROTOCELLS. FOUR RESEARCH OBJECTIVES ARE PROPOSED: (1) IDENTIFY AND CHARACTERIZE POTENTIAL NON-MEMBRANOUS COMPARTMENTS (NMCS) FOR CONCENTRATING RNA FROM DILUTE SOLUTION AND DRIVING RNA BASE PAIRING. (2) TEST THESE COMPARTMENTS FOR THEIR ABILITY TO FACILITATE FUNCTION OF KNOWN FUNCTIONAL RNAS. (3) TAKE THOSE COMPARTMENTS FROM OBJECTIVES 1 AND 2 THAT BEST FACILITATE RNA FUNCTION AND TEST FOR THEIR ABILITY TO FACILITATE THE EVOLUTION OF ENHANCED RIBOZYME FUNCTION. (4) ENCAPSULATE THE NMCS INSIDE OF PROGENITOR MEMBRANES. OUR NMCS WILL BE POLYMER-RICH AQUEOUS DROPLETS FORMED BY PHASE SEPARATION. THE PRIMARY FUNCTION TO BE ASSAYED HEREIN IS GAIN OF ENZYMATIC ACTIVITY IN RIBOZYMES, EITHER FROM VERY DILUTE REAGENTS OR BY FACILITATING NATIVE RNA FOLDING (I.E. ACTING AS AN PRIMORDIAL RNA CHAPERONE) AND PRODUCT RELEASE IN MULTIPLE TURNOVER RNA ENZYMES. WE HYPOTHESIZE THAT CLASSES OF RIBOZYMES THAT DID NOT EMERGE IN CONVENTIONAL SELECTION CONDITIONS WILL BE ISOLATED; HIGH-THROUGHPUT SEQUENCING WILL BE USED TO COVER EXCEPTIONAL SEQUENCE SPACE IN SEARCH OF THESE. RNA-CONTAINING NMCS WILL BE STABILIZED AGAINST COALESCENCE BY NANOSCALE AMPHIPHILE ASSEMBLIES ADSORBED AT THE AQUEOUS/AQUEOUS PHASE BOUNDARY. THE RESULTING SEMI-PERMEABLE BOUNDARY WILL NOT BE A BILAYER AND HENCE SHOULD BE AMENABLE TO BOTH FORMATION IN HIGH SALT AND PASSAGE OF LARGE MOLECULES. WE HYPOTHESIZE THAT SUCH A BARRIER COULD SERVE AS A STEP TOWARDS FORMING TRUE BILAYER MEMBRANES THAT ENTRAP AND ENRICH FUNCTIONAL MOLECULES. COLLECTIVELY, THE WORK PROPOSED HERE WILL INVESTIGATE HOW DILUTE, POTENTIALLY CATALYTIC MACROMOLECULES ON PREBIOTIC EARTH COULD HAVE BEEN CONCENTRATED INTO NMCS AND HOW THEIR LOCAL ENVIRONMENT COULD HAVE FACILITATED FOLDING AND CATALYTIC FUNCTION. REGARDING RNA ENZYMES HAVING MULTIPLE TURNOVER, WHICH IS KEY TO LIFE, WE WILL EXPLORE HOW NMCS COULD HAVE CONCENTRATED VERY DILUTE ENZYMES AND SUBSTRATES, AND FACILITATED THE RELEASE OF PRODUCTS FROM THEIR TEMPLATES. THE MAIN SIGNIFICANCE OF OUR FINDINGS FROM AN RNA ENZYME POINT OF VIEW WILL BE TO DEVELOP NOVEL CONCEPTUAL FRAMEWORKS FOR HOW NMCS COULD: (1) CHAPERONE RNA FOLDING, (2) FACILITATE MULTIPLE TURNOVER OF RNA ENZYMES, AND (3) AID IN THE EVOLUTION OF NEW CATALYTIC RNAS.
